	   <a name=10112161413266></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10112161413266><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=10112161413266>RE: Keeping skills capped</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=10112161413266#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=48387><span id=Sage>Botten the Wise</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>32 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jan 16th 4:22 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>My experiences as a cleric since the time of my post (My level is 37 now) have taught me a thing or two about the way of the healer. So, I am going to beg to differ with the aforementioned approach.<br><br>There isn't anything wrong with the approach mentioned, but I would like to present the advantages of a meleeing cleric. Really, it just comes down to a difference in style.<br><br>I assert that a good cleric SHOULD melee. However, I believe that a cleric should not melee unless full of mana. A cleric is at his best when the mana is ready to be spent wisely.<br><br>Here are my reasons to melee when full of mana:<br><br>1) Extra Damage. A cleric doesn't do as much damage as the other classes, but anything that will make a fight shorter is a GOOD thing.<br><br>2) Free AC. A cleric WILL get pounded on from time to time whether you melee or not. Not many people seem to know it, but whenever you raise your DEFENSE attribute your base AC goes up. DEFENSE can only be raised by having a mob pound on you. Melee away! I'd rather get hit a few times while meleeing to raise my DEFENSE (and thus, my AC) than pay hundreds or thousands of platinum later on to get my AC to a respectable (and survivable) level.<br><br>3) Yard Trash Adds. Have you ever been medding up your mana when you were aggroed on by some pesky greenie? Why waste mana that you were trying to regain when you can just dispatch the trash with a few well placed blows?<br><br>4) Image/Group Playing. Would you rather share your hard earned coin and items with a group member that doesn't want to get their hands dirty or one who isn't afraid to wade into the thick of things and help out? Sure, a healer is there to heal, but why not go the extra mile? Many have been surprised (pleasantly) when I melee, and have complimented me on it.<br><br>Let me say again, that there is no right or wrong way for a cleric to do his job (as long as everyone survives). It's ok to just heal. It's ok to throw your DDs during a fight. It's ok to melee.<br><br>It's all a preference of style.<br>&nbsp;<br>Botten Baggens<br>6 Earthen Lane<br>Rivervale<br>Saryrn<br><br>Galius Dalmatius<br>N. Freeport<br>Saryrn</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
