	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Agi influences ac and being hit/missed.&nbsp;&nbsp;A characters agi has no bearing on whether or not he'll hit or miss his opponent.  Dex and str will help raise offensive skills (as should wis/int whichever is higher), Agi does the opposite, helps increase def and dodge type skills but won't make a player dodge more (with the skill), but if enough agi, could help mob just plain miss you more often.  However, when Agi is 75+, it doesn't make a big difference, you need a LOT of it to notice a change in mobs hitting you, though it never hurts either!  =)  Beware Agi below 75, as you take a huge ac hit.  AC is definately a clerics best friend next to wis/mana, and sometimes moreso depending on where he/she is atm.<br>&nbsp;<br>Gestalt<br>60 Grandmaster<br>ARo</td></tr>
