	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you're a cleric on welfare like me, there are a few cheap options for equip. Split paw gloves sell for around 10pp from players and give 4 ac 3 dex and 2 wis. Bronze goes cheap these days, load up into any slots you can. Also, try gathering up your food stamps and saving up for a small wisdom deity, these give 2 WIS and fit in the range slot, they sell for 100pp in east commons on Bristlebane. For a shield, camp the gnolls in Highpass to get your CDS, which is the best you'll find until the guardian shield, or else do the Testament quest (a real pain in the patookus if you ask me). The gnolls also drop the PGT which you can't use but sells for around 100pp. Oh ya, look into a polished bone bracer, 2 AC and 3 WIS, sells for 100pp.<br><br>As far as weapons go, head on over to the forest giant fort in Warsilk Woods and /shout that you're looking for a forest giant hammer. These are NO DROP so giant hunters will let you loot one. They're dmg 10 and delay 35, and have a cool graphic. Or else get a EBM for 100pp.. good luck, clerics are an expensive class, but they rake in the cash starting at lvl 39 :)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
